sequenceDiagram
    participant "Backend API" as BackendAPI
    participant "PostgreSQL DB" as PostgreSQLDB
    participant "Stripe Connect API" as StripeConnectAPI
    participant "AWS SES" as AWSSES

    activate BackendAPI
    BackendAPI->>BackendAPI: 1. 1. Admin triggers invoice creation for 'Awarded' project (e.g., POST /api/v1/projects/{id}/invoices)
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDB: 2. 2. Get Project, Client & Invoice details
    PostgreSQLDB-->>BackendAPI: Project, Client, Invoice data
    BackendAPI->>StripeConnectAPI: 3. 3. Create Stripe Checkout Session
    StripeConnectAPI-->>BackendAPI: Checkout Session object (id, url)
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDB: 4. 4. Persist Stripe Session ID to Invoice record
    PostgreSQLDB-->>BackendAPI: Rows affected
    BackendAPI->>AWSSES: 5. 5. Send invoice email with payment link
    AWSSES-->>BackendAPI: SES Message ID
    StripeConnectAPI->>BackendAPI: 6. 6. [Asynchronous] Client completes payment; Stripe sends webhook event
    BackendAPI-->>StripeConnectAPI: HTTP 200 OK (synchronous response to webhook)
    BackendAPI->>BackendAPI: 7. 6a. Verify webhook signature using secret
    BackendAPI-->>BackendAPI: Boolean: isValid
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDB: 8. 6b. Check for existing Stripe Event ID for idempotency
    PostgreSQLDB-->>BackendAPI: Boolean: exists
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDB: 9. 6c. Execute payment processing as atomic transaction
    PostgreSQLDB-->>BackendAPI: Transaction committed

    note over PostgreSQLDB: REQ-BUS-001: The update of the project status to 'Active' is contingent on the successful complet...

    deactivate BackendAPI
